data(chimpanzees)
d <- chimpanzees
d$block_id <- d$block
d$treatment <- 1L + d$prosoc_left + 2L*d$condition
dat_list <- list(
    pulled_left = d$pulled_left,
    actor = d$actor,
    block_id = d$block,
    treatment = as.integer(d$treatment) )

m11.4ulam <- ulam(
    alist(
        pulled_left ~ dbinom( 1 , p ) ,
        logit(p) <- a[actor] + b[treatment] ,
        a[actor] ~ dnorm( 0 , 1.5 ),
        b[treatment] ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.5 )
    ) , data=dat_list , chains=4 , log_lik=TRUE )

First we need to create dummy variables with 1 for large, 0 for small and 1 for adult, 0 for immature.
We need to transform the variables P (size of pirate ) ,A (age of the pirate) and V (size of the victim).
y = number of success
n = total number of trials
Then the probability is Y/n

library(fastDummies)

pir2$success<-pir2$y/pir2$n
mod_pirate <- quap(alist(
    y ~ dbinom(n, p),
    logit(p) <- a + bp*P_L + ba*A_A + bv*V_L,
    a ~ dnorm(0, 10),
    bp ~ dnorm(0, 5),
    bv ~ dnorm(0, 5),
    ba ~ dnorm(0, 5)
  ), data=pir2)
precis(mod_pirate, depth=2 )
